- Use yarn for package and project management
- Store all persistent data as JSON files in Cloudflare R2; do not use SQL or NoSQL databases.
- Only use Clerk for authentication, and support Google/Facebook OAuth from day 1.
- Do not add infrastructure or features that would incur non-trivial costs without explicit discussion.
- All features must be accessible and understandable by non-technical users; prioritize usability and clarity.
- Both photo and video gallery functionality must be available at launch.
- Organize all uploaded content by EXIF creation date in a timeline view.
- Admin-only features must never be exposed to regular users.
